name: Rob Burrow
summary: Former rugby star and tireless campaigner against motor neurone disease (MND), Rob Burrow, has passed away at the age of 41. The Leeds Rhinos legend, who was diagnosed with MND in 2019, dedicated the last years of his life to raising awareness and funds for the debilitating condition. His unwavering spirit and determination inspired countless individuals, including the likes of Prince William and Kevin Sinfield, who have paid heartfelt tributes to his legacy. The rugby community and beyond join in mourning the loss of a true warrior and a symbol of hope in the fight against MND.

name: Tsitsipas
summary: Stefanos Tsitsipas and Andrey Rublev have progressed through to the fourth round of Roland Garros. Tsitsipas defeated Zhang Zhizhen in straight sets, while Rublev advanced with a win over Emil Ruusuvuori. Tsitsipas and Paula Badosa, who recently reconciled after a brief split, are now competing in mixed doubles at Roland Garros. Other notable players who have advanced include Iga Swiatek, Coco Gauff, Carlos Alcaraz, and Jannik Sinner. On Sunday, Tsitsipas will face Lorenzo Sonego, while Arnaldi will play Karen Khachanov, and Dimitrov and Hurkacz will also be in action. In the quarter-finals, Alcaraz and Tsitsipas have set up a potential clash, while Sinner will take on Grigor Dimitrov.

name: Kokkinakis
summary: During the 2024 French Open, Thanasi Kokkinakis had a remarkable run. Despite losing the first two sets to Lorenzo Giustino, Kokkinakis fought back to win the third set in a tiebreak. The Australian then faced Giulio Zeppieri, rallying from 0-2 down to secure a thrilling five-set victory. However, his run came to an end when he lost to Taylor Fritz in the third round. Despite the disappointing result, Kokkinakis' performance was praised by commentators, with many highlighting his determination and resilience.

summary: News headlines highlight various events and issues related to Phoenix, Arizona. Phoenix Labs has laid off over 160 employees in the Bay Area amid ongoing cuts in the video game industry. In a positive note, Keystone Phoenix has set a Cumberland record in harness racing. The Phoenix Zoo has announced extended summer hours. WestJet will compensate a Kelowna man for a flight delay to Phoenix. A new residential project, The Phoenix, by Feldman Architecture, is showcased.
